==English==

===Alternative forms===
* [[acclimatise]] {{qualifier|chiefly British}}

===Etymology===
{{suffix|acclimate|ize}}. First attested in 1836.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɘ.ˈklaɪ.mə.ˌtaɪz/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|acclimatiz|ing}}

# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To get [[used]] to a new [[climate]].
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To make used to a new [[climate]] or one that is different from that which is [[natural]]; to [[inure]] or [[habituate]] to other [[circumstance]]s; to [[adapt]] to the [[peculiarities]] of a foreign or strange [[climate]].

====Usage notes====
Has become more common in use than [[acclimate]].

====Derived terms====
* [[acclimatization]]
* [[acclimatizer]]

====Related terms====
